5. Architecture Confirmation
NO supervisor/router node that picks which agent handles a request.

The flow is deterministic and linear:


START
  ↓
parse_intent_node → infers persona from keywords
  ↓
permission_check_node → checks if user has permission for selected collection
  ↓
permission_router (conditional) → routes based on has_permission + selected_agent_role
  ↓
├─→ permission_blocked → END (if no permission)
├─→ creator_agent → END (if creator)
├─→ reviewer_agent → END (if reviewer)
└─→ approver_agent → END (if approver)
Key points:
No intent-based agent selection beyond the initial parse_intent - the router only decides which of the 3 agent nodes to call based on selected_agent_role

Every request goes through the same pipeline:

parse_intent_node → keyword matching (CREATOR/FILLER/APPROVER/QUERY keywords)
permission_check_node → validates against user's collection_agents
One of [creator_agent, reviewer_agent, approver_agent] based on inferred/selected persona
END
The permission_router is NOT a supervisor - it's a simple conditional that checks:

If has_permission == False → route to permission_blocked
If has_permission == True → route to the agent matching selected_agent_role
No dynamic routing based on request content after the initial parse - once the persona is inferred, the path is fixed

